I believe this is coming from PrepBulkImport code below.  Only ".map" and ".rf" files are good to process.  Maybe to best this is to remove the "warning message" completely since we know that other types of files will be there or change the message to something like "{} exempt from processing, ignoring", fileStatus.getPath()

```java
for (FileStatus file : files) {
      final FileStatus fileStatus = file;
      final Path originalPath = fileStatus.getPath();
      String[] fileNameParts = originalPath.getName().split("\\.");
      String extension = "";
      boolean invalidFileName;
      if (fileNameParts.length > 1) {
        extension = fileNameParts[fileNameParts.length - 1];
        invalidFileName = !FileOperations.getValidExtensions().contains(extension);
      } else {
        invalidFileName = true;
      }
      if (invalidFileName) {
        log.warn("{} does not have a valid extension, ignoring", fileStatus.getPath());
        continue;
      }
```

